<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Fletcher's shop open for business...txt</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Erilar">Erilar</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:10 a.m. 19/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Fletcher's shop open for business...txt<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/mithaniel_marr.cgi?read=39" TARGET=_self>Fletcher's shop open for business...txt</A> (Algeran)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>I'm a 6th level ranger hailing from Kelethin. I can also attest to the usefulness of a bow, although I'm only using a Hunter's Bow and silver-piece arrows. My skill is nowhere near enough to do any damage - only a few points. Even so, the bow is still quite useful to me for drawing monsters in from a distance, such as when playing "safari guide" for your party.

<P>Algeran - any advice on getting one's archery skill up? Basically, I can only ever get 1 shot in before the creature charges me. Is there a way to get more shots off for additional practice?
<P>Also, how about some words of wisdom for budding fletchers? As in, how does one get started, what equipment is necessary, etc.
<P>Good hunting all,
<BR>Erilar
<P>&gt; Okay, so my skill in fletching skill has
<BR>&gt; imporved nicely. Now I just need to sell
<BR>&gt; some bows and arrows. The cost of making a
<BR>&gt; nice bow is very high. I mean until you use
<BR>&gt; at least an Elm bow, the bow doesn't seem
<BR>&gt; like it is worth the time invested in
<BR>&gt; gaining skill in archery. Hickery is ok (10
<BR>&gt; dam) but the 50 range is too short. ( you
<BR>&gt; can just about kiss that grizzley before you
<BR>&gt; can shoot.) So who whould pay 4 or 5 plat
<BR>&gt; for the elm bow? I haven't found anyone yet.
<BR>&gt; Now when I am able to make the Oak and
<BR>&gt; better bows, at least I can tell people the
<BR>&gt; damage I hit to make their mouth water. But
<BR>&gt; wow is that oak expensive. over 17 plat for
<BR>&gt; the staff alone. So again, who would pay 20
<BR>&gt; to 40 plat for an oak bow. Well I must try
<BR>&gt; to incent people so here you go :
<P>&gt; Well, all I can say is that I am dedicated
<BR>&gt; to the fletching proffesion. And I would
<BR>&gt; like to get the people's interested in this
<BR>&gt; great art. So.... here is the deal:
<P>&gt; 1) Hickery bows will be given to anyone who
<BR>&gt; wants one. Just send me a tell, and come and
<BR>&gt; pick it up. There is one catch, I will ask
<BR>&gt; you to purchase your arrows from only me. I
<BR>&gt; will make any arrow you will like (for a
<BR>&gt; price), and for that promise I will give you
<BR>&gt; 10 point 1 arrows to start you archery
<BR>&gt; carrer off for free.
<P>&gt; 2) I will sell Elm bows at an EXTREEMLY good
<BR>&gt; price: 13 dam, 51 delay, 75 range - 3plat
<BR>&gt; 5gold I will make better quality bows on
<BR>&gt; demand, but remember that better quality
<BR>&gt; mean faster delay and less damage. example:
<BR>&gt; carved elm bow is 12dam, 47delay, 75 range -
<BR>&gt; and it cost 2plat more to make. I have used
<BR>&gt; both, and the carved is better, but you must
<BR>&gt; decide if it is worth the extra cost.
<P>&gt; 3) Arrows at very good prices: I will be
<BR>&gt; more than happy to make arrows of different
<BR>&gt; variety for you. Class 2 bone point with 2
<BR>&gt; damage and 125 range is a very nice arrow
<BR>&gt; and the lowest cost (5 silver) each. 3dam
<BR>&gt; 125 range hooked bone arrows are going for
<BR>&gt; (2gold) each. Please compare these prices to
<BR>&gt; the arrows you can buy at the shop. This is
<BR>&gt; VERY aggresive pricing. If I fail just a
<BR>&gt; couple of times, I will lose money.
<P>&gt; Recomended techniques:
<P>&gt; Why fight with a bow:
<P>&gt; Can a warrior use any other weapon to draw a
<BR>&gt; prey from far away, no How about doing 40-50
<BR>&gt; dam to a creature before melee. (stronger
<BR>&gt; bows) think about the future. Rangers - try
<BR>&gt; root or snare and hit with the bow will
<BR>&gt; backing up if the creature is not fully
<BR>&gt; frozen, I have done this very successfully
<BR>&gt; getting in 30-80 damage before melee (and my
<BR>&gt; archery is only 23)
<P>&gt; Well this is to generate some demand for my
<BR>&gt; art, I hope to see you in Narrath. I can be
<BR>&gt; in the Sure Fall Glade,
<P>&gt; Qeynos are usually.
<P>&gt; Good Travels,
<P>&gt; Algeran
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
